# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or not
#   install all needed dependencies.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   This is especially recommended for binary packages to ensure reproducibility, and is more
#   commonly ignored for libraries.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
#pdm.lock
#   pdm stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml, but it is recommended to not include it
#   in version control.
#   https://pdm.fming.dev/#use-with-ide
.pdm.toml

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/David-OConnor/pyflow and github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

# Celery stuff
celerybeat-schedule
celerybeat.pid

# SageMath parsed files
*.sage.py

# Environments
.env
.env.vm
.phantom-agent/
.venv
env/
venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/

# Manual pre-release backups (created when nuking phantom-vm before
# a destructive upgrade — e.g. .backup-pre-v0.4.0/). Local-only;
# never committed.
.backup-pre-*/

# Workstation-local artifacts: screenshots, session-transcript exports,
# experimental skill clones, scratch HTML / Excalidraw files. These
# accumulate during dev work and should never travel into the repo.
*.png
!mcp/agent/public/**/*.png
!installer/**/*.png
!docs/**/*.png
# v0.9.4 — bundled vendor logos for the cortex-content data-sources catalog.
# 93 PNG files extracted from demisto/content during the v0.8.1 bake.
# Without this exception the global `*.png` rule silently dropped them
# from git tracking → they never landed in the agent image → operators saw
# 93 of 197 marketplace cards with no vendor logo since v0.8.1.
!bundles/spark/connectors/cortex-content/baked/**/*.png
# Leading slash so this matches ONLY the top-level scratch directory.
# Without it, the pattern also catches mcp/agent/components/diagrams/
# (the legitimate React component diagrams folder) — every new auth /
# topology / pipeline SVG component gets silently ignored on first add.
# Caught the trap when auth-topology.tsx wouldn't show in git status.
/diagrams/
# Leading slash for the same reason as /diagrams/ above — bare `tests/`
# silently ignores bundles/spark/mcp/tests/ (the embedded MCP pytest
# suite). Pre-v0.6.53 the suite's 28 existing files were tracked
# because the rule predated them, but new files got dropped. Caught
# while adding test_kb_loader.py in v0.6.53; fixed the pattern at the
# same time so it stops biting future test additions.
/tests/
*.excalidraw
topology-excalidraw.html
index.html
svg-only.html
.serena/
excalidraw-diagram-skill/
snow-agent-complete/

